\begin_layout Standard
The initial objective of this thesis was to study the angle dependence of
 the spectrum for the regions of dominant AA-stacking in twisted bilayer
 graphene using a continuum method.
 These regions are hexagonal, which means that we must first find a way
 to solve the Dirac-Weyl equation in polygonal enclosures.
\end_layout

