\det\left[h_{n,m}\left(qc\right)\right]=\det\left[\frac{1}{2\pi}\int_{0}^{2\pi}d\theta e^{-i\left(n+m\right)\theta}\mathcal{J}_{-m}\left[qc\rho_{k}\left(\theta\right)\right]\right]
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unfortunately, this method failed to provide a spectrum that was satisfactory
 for any matrix size tested.
 As such, we need to find a different method to treat the edges.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
More Suitable Coordinates?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Suppose now that we want to solve Schr
