\begin_inset Formula $\theta\in\left[-\frac{\pi}{n},\frac{\pi}{n}\right]$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\left[0,a\right]$
\end_inset

 with periodic boundary conditions 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi\left(x,-\frac{\pi}{n}\right)=\psi\left(x,\frac{\pi}{n}\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi\left(a,\theta\right)=0$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 is the number of sides of the polygon we want to decompose in triangular
 wedges, as seen in Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:wedge"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
