\begin_layout Standard
The obtained spinor is given by (ignoring any multiplicative constants)
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\Psi_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(\pm,j\right)}\left(\overrightarrow{r}\right)=\left(\begin{array}{c}
1\\
0
\end{array}\right)\phi_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(j\right)}\left(\overrightarrow{r}\right)+\left(\begin{array}{c}
0\\
1
