\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(j\right)}\left(\overrightarrow{r}\right)$
\end_inset

 is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\phi_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(j\right)}\left(x,y\right)=\begin{cases}
\mathcal{C}_{1}\left\{ -\sin\left[q\left(n_{2}+2n_{1}\right)x\right]\sin\left[\sqrt{3}qn_{2}y\right]+\sin\left[q\left(n_{1}+2n_{2}\right)x\right]\sin\left[\sqrt{3}qn_{1}y\right]+\right.\\
\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\left.+\sin\left[q\left(n_{1}-n_{2}\right)x\right]\sin\left[\sqrt{3}q\left(n_{2}+n_{1}\right)y\right]\right\} , & j=1\\
\\
\mathcal{C}_{2}\left\{ -\cos\left[q\left(n_{2}+2n_{1}\right)x\right]\sin\left[\sqrt{3}qn_{2}y\right]-\cos\left[q\left(n_{1}+2n_{2}\right)x\right]\sin\left[\sqrt{3}qn_{1}y\right]+\right.\\
\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\left.+\cos\left[q\left(n_{1}-n_{2}\right)x\right]\sin\left[\sqrt{3}q\left(n_{2}+n_{1}\right)y\right]\right\} , & j=2
\end{cases}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After this, we want to analyze the spectrum of this equation, as well as
