\begin_inset Formula $N_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(\pm\right)}$
\end_inset

 is the normalization constant given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(\pm\right)}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
\]

\end_inset

As before, 
\begin_inset Formula $\chi_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(\pm,j\right)}$
\end_inset

 is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\chi_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(\pm,j\right)}=\eta_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(\pm\right)}\left(\partial_{y}-i\partial_{x}\right)\phi_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(j\right)}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

with 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\eta_{n_{1},n_{2}}^{\left(\pm\right)}=\frac{1}{\pm\frac{4\pi}{3L}\sqrt{\left(n_{1}^{2}+n_{2}^{2}+n_{1}n_{2}\right)}}
\]

\end_inset

By substitution on 
